UPSTREAM-DERIVED — Copyright 2022 wataru-okada et al., MIT License
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Read-only mirror of the upstream repository (unmodified):
  upstream/                 — pristine git clone of w-okada/voice-changer
  upstream/LICENSE          — original MIT license text (DO NOT MODIFY)

Vendored and *trimmed* from upstream (modifications are MIT, attribution
required if redistributed):
  src/server/               — entire subtree

The src/server/ directory was created by:
  1. Copying upstream/server/ into src/server/.
  2. Deleting non-RVC engine subdirectories: Beatrice/, DDSP_SVC/,
     DiffusionSVC/, EasyVC/, LLVC/, MMVCv13/, MMVCv15/, SoVitsSvc40/.
  3. Deleting the V1 VoiceChanger.py.
  4. Removing the rmvpe model from DiffusionSVC and re-homing it under
     RVC/pitchExtractor/rmvpe/ (see commit history).
  5. Surgical removal of Mac/Windows code paths (WASAPI, _MEIPASS,
     native-client launchers, etc.).
  6. Pruning of dead engine references in const.py, ModelSlot.py,
     VoiceChangerManager.py, VoiceChangerV2.py, SampleDownloader.py.

The trimming changes are detailed in CHANGELOG.md under "Phase 1 — Lean Core".
The original copyright notices on upstream files inside src/server/ are
preserved where present.


